race.comment: DURAZZO (5) is the clear top pick in the Conquering Stakes. Has placed 2/3 in Stakes grade and missed a whisker the other. Has been heavily bet and sharp both starts this preparation, and the mile suits. Maps to get every chance. Tougher sorting out the remainder. ALVARINHO (12) won a decent race first-up and then was beaten 2L behind the above in the stronger Newmarket. She's a quinella hope with the extra fitness. BANK MAUR (1) is a Group 2 winning Queenslander in the Laming yard, and he's prepared for this with a first-up hit-out in the Cranbourne Cup over a mile. Wasn't too far away in the Eye Liner Stakes at Ipswich three back, and that effort would have him in the finish. Has an awkward gate, but Newitt's booking suggests he's pleasing. FIRST ACCUSED (2) resumed in the DURAZZO race and looked a run short. Proved second-up and the veteran is a 3x Stakes winner. In the mix.
